Name: Red Barn Robotics
Headline: A Roomba for weeds on a farm.
Description: We are building an autonomous robot to precisely eliminate weeds and leave crops untouched. Despite $100 billion being spent annually on weed control, weeds still cost the US economy $46B/year. Weeds steal sunlight and nutrients from crops, forcing farmers to choose between higher costs and lower yields. Moreover, many farms still rely on hand labor to control weed growth. The process is slow, expensive, and increasingly difficult due to constant labor shortages (1 out of every 5 US farm positions go unfilled each year). Our robot nicknamed the Field Hand is able to automate one of the worst jobs on a farm and will help healthily feed the world.

# Weeding Made Easy
Red Barn Robotics provides autonomous intra-row weeding services to help farmers increase yields and reduce their labor costs
[Contact SalesContact Sales![icon](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2a04_arrow-corner-dark.svg)![icon](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2a04_arrow-corner-dark.svg)](https://www.redbarnrobotics.com/</contact-us>)
![photo](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2a26_pexels-zen-chung-5528939.webp)
## Meet the Field Hand
The reliable, tireless worker your farm has been waiting for. Our autonomous weeding robot is built to keep your fields weed-free and is ready to start working on your farm.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4eeae49723f370e316ac_Bulls%20Eye.svg)
##### Precise
Eliminates intra-row weeds typically reserved for hand weeding crews with no human intervention
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4ee84e5c50b1423a136f_Computer%20Brain.png)
##### Autonomous
Navigates under its own power and does not require any additional equipment or guidance to navigate between fields
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4ee86f9a473d724a3a96_Gear.png)
##### Configurable
A modular design allows us to choose the tools that best fits the unique constraints of your farm
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4ee879d23ae17f1a7917_Globe.png)
##### Sustainable
A lightweight design prevents compaction while mechanical cultivation preserves soil health
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c464348e62cb35865fe3b_Isometric%20robot%20no%20background%20\(1\).png)
## Our Weeding Service
1
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4ee9c6f70da34c4b069b_Quote%20Bubbles.png)
#### Schedule a Consultation
Schedule a time for you to tell us about your farm, crops, and weeding needs so we can assess how to help
2
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4ee8ec38f94fd6e80a77_White%20Map.png)
#### Get a Custom Weeding Plan
We map your fields and create a tailored weeding schedule based on your crop type, bed configuration and growth cycle
3
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4ee8edaaec65ab03024c_Cycle.png)
#### We Handle the Operations
Our robots arrive at your farm and get to work removing weeds according to your custom weeding plan
4
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679d4eebe49723f370e316f1_Plant.png)
#### Stay Weed-Free All Season
With regular service throughout the growing season, we keep your fields weed-free—no extra labor or equipment required.
[Contact SalesContact Sales![icon](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2a04_arrow-corner-dark.svg)![icon](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2a04_arrow-corner-dark.svg)](https://www.redbarnrobotics.com/</contact-us>)
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c2855a08dd9ef1ec51a43_FH%20with%20Weeders%20\(1\).jpg)
## Tired of hand weeding?
Labor shortages and rising costs are making hand weeding more expensive than ever. At Red Barn Robotics, we’re changing the game with our autonomous weeding robot—built to eliminate weeds efficiently, reliably, and at a lower cost than manual labor.
[Contact SalesContact Sales![icon](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d29f2_right-up-small-w.svg)![icon](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d2854/679c26bf7f96c23ec67d29f2_right-up-small-w.svg)](https://www.redbarnrobotics.com/</contact-us>)
## full transparency when it comes to our practices
We take great pride in our sustainable farming practices. By using natural methods of pest control, crop rotation, and organic fertilizers, we ensure that our produce is not only safe to eat but also rich in flavor and nutrients. Our commitment to sustainability extends beyond our fields; we strive to reduce waste, and protect the local ecosystem.

**Red Barn Robotics: A New Era in Weeding Technology**

Founded in 2023 and nestled in Seattle, WA, Red Barn Robotics is on a mission to revolutionize weed control in agriculture with an innovative solution that’s simple yet powerful—think of it as a Roomba, but for weeds. Officially part of the Y Combinator Batch W25, this startup is tackling a pervasive issue in farming: the $100 billion industry dedicated to weed control, which still leads to a staggering economic burden of $46 billion annually in the U.S. due to decreased crop yields.

Weeds are not just a nuisance; they siphon off essential sunlight and nutrients from crops, and with labor shortages plaguing the agriculture sector—one in five farm jobs remains unfilled—farmers often find themselves in a tough bind, either paying more or yielding less. Enter the “Field Hand,” Red Barn's autonomous robot designed specifically to weed crops with precision, all while leaving the crops untouched. This automation frees up farmers from one of the most labor-intensive and costly burdens of farming, paving the way for more sustainable practices.

With a lean team of three, including their Group Partner Brad Flora, Red Barn Robotics embodies the sprint of modern startups, combining innovative robotics with a commitment to sustainable farming practices. They emphasize using lightweight machinery to minimize soil compaction, ensuring health for both the crops and the ecosystem.

Red Barn Robotics isn't just about pulling weeds; it's about creating a reliable, efficient, and sustainable way for farmers to manage their land. Their service model includes a tailored approach where they consult with farmers to devise custom weeding plans, ensuring that their technology aligns with the unique needs of each farm. Through regular seasonal services, they promise to keep fields weed-free without the need for additional labor or heavy equipment.

In an industry often stuck in outdated methods, Red Barn Robotics is more than just a tech company—it’s a forward-thinking solution that aims to help farmers feed a growing world sustainably. Curious about their approach or want to learn more? Check them out at [Red Barn Robotics](https://www.redbarnrobotics.com).
